# Dashboard Compact Layout Plan

## Goal
Fit the main Dashboard content within the initial viewport ("first screen") to minimize scrolling and improve information density.

## User Review Required
> [!NOTE]
> I will be reducing the size of the Mascot and vertical spacing (gaps, margins, padding) to make the layout more compact.

## Proposed Changes

### CSS Styles
#### [MODIFY] [App.css](file:///c:/Users/admin/.gemini/스위치웹서비스/daily-habit-tracker/src/App.css)
- **Container**: Reduce `gap` (24px -> 16px).
- **Header**: Reduce `margin-top` and `gap`.
- **Mascot**: Reduce `font-size` (80px -> 60px).
- **Title**: Reduce `font-size` (28px -> 24px).
- **Progress Section**: Reduce `padding` (20px -> 16px).
- **Add Habit Form**: Reduce `padding` and input/button size.
- **Habit List**: Decrease gap between cards.
- **Habit Card**: Reduce `padding` (16px -> 12px).

#### [MODIFY] [index.css](file:///c:/Users/admin/.gemini/스위치웹서비스/daily-habit-tracker/src/index.css)
- **Root**: Reduce `padding` (24px -> 16px) for mobile-first optimization.

## Verification Plan
1.  **Visual Check**: Open the Dashboard and observe if the habit list and key elements are visible without scrolling (depending on screen height).
2.  **Functionality**: Ensure touch targets (buttons, checkboxes) remain usable despite slightly smaller padding.
